article.description: — Tyler Whitney-Sidney scored 16 points as Lehigh beat Loyola Maryland 75-70 on Saturday.
article.headline: Lehigh secures 75-70 win over Loyola Maryland
article.linkText: Lehigh secures 75-70 win over Loyola Maryland
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- — Tyler Whitney-Sidney scored 16 points as Lehigh beat Loyola Maryland 75-70 on Saturday. Dominic Parolin scored 15 points and added eight rebounds for the Mountain Hawks (10-15, 7-7 Patriot League). Burke Chebuhar had 14 points and shot 5 for 9 (2 for 3 from 3-point range) and 2 of 3 from the free throw line. The Greyhounds (6-21, 4-10) were led in scoring by Deon Perry, who finished with 33 points, four assists and three steals. Golden Dike added 14 points for Loyola. Alonso Faure also recorded 13 points and 12 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
